{{Quote|I've seen many different ways of making a photon fizzle, but no one did it better than Doodnik.|Dexter Jettster|<ref name="Dining at Dex's" />}}
'''Doodnik Sharpelz''' was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Jillsarian/Legends|Jillsarian]] who worked as a [[Bartender/Legends|bartender]] and [[Chef/Legends|chef]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tyne's Horky]]. Originally from the planet [[Ojom/Legends|Ojom]], he left his [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] before [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]] and found bartending work on Tyne's Horky alongside his old friend [[Dexter Jettster/Legends|Dexter Jettster]]. By [[15 BBY/Legends|15 BBY]], he had opened [[Doodnik's Café]] in the world's eponymous [[Tyne's Horky (town)|mining town]], where he worked in the kitchen and entertained such customers as the local [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Kleb Zellock]]. In that [[Standard year/Legends|year]], Sharpelz hired the [[Droid/Legends|droids]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] to work for him as [[Waiter/Legends|waiters]], but the incompetence of the duo prompted a furious Sharpelz to fire them both on their first [[Standard day/Legends|day]].

==Biography==
{{Quote|Out, out, out! And don't come back!|Doodnik Sharpelz, after firing C-3PO and R2-D2|<ref name="The Lost Prince" />}}
[[File:Doodnik-TLP.png|thumb|right|300px|Doodnik angrily reacts to C-3PO's hijinks.]]
Doodnik Sharpelz was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Jillsarian/Legends|Jillsarian]] who was raised by adoptive natives on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Ojom/Legends|Ojom]].<ref name="Re-Animated Part 2" /> He was friends with the [[Besalisk/Legends|Besalisk]] [[Dexter Jettster/Legends|Dexter Jettster]], and,<ref name="Dining at Dex's" /> before the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]],<ref name="Date">In "[[Dining at Dex's]]," [[Dexter Jettster/Legends|Dexter Jettster]] is working at [[Dex's Diner/Legends|Dex's Diner]] and recounting his days with Doodnik Sharpelz. The diner's [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]] destruction is featured in ''[[The Last of the Jedi: Underworld]]''.</ref> the two of them left their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] and found employment as [[Bartender/Legends|bartenders]] on [[Tyne's Horky]],<ref name="Dining at Dex's" /> a [[Mining/Legends|mining]] world located on the [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] frontier.<ref name="Tyne's Horky db">{{DB|location|tyneshorky|Tyne's Horky}}</ref> Working together, Sharpelz and Jettster prepared such drinks as [[photon fizzle]]s, [[giva jumbo]]s, and [[circuit cider]].<ref name="Dining at Dex's" />

By [[15 BBY/Legends|15 BBY]],<ref name="Polyhedron">{{PolyhedronCite|170|Star Wars Droids: The Adventures of R2-D2 and C-3PO}}</ref> Sharpelz had made a deal with the [[Dirconite]] [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenary]] [[Kleb Zellock]] and become part-owner of a [[Restaurant/Legends|restaurant]]<ref name="Re-Animated Part 2" /> and [[Tapcafe/Legends|tapcafe]]<ref name="CSWE" /> in a lawless mining [[City/Legends|town]] also called [[Tyne's Horky (town)|Tyne's Horky]].<ref name="Storybook" /> Although the Jillsarian was the proprietor<ref name="CSWE" /> of [[Doodnik's Café]], Zellock, as the leader of the planet's criminal underworld, used the establishment as his base of [[Kleb Zellock's criminal empire|operations]].<ref name="Kleb Zellock db">{{DB|character|klebzellock|Zellock, Kleb}}</ref> Sharpelz worked as a [[Chef/Legends|chef]] in the kitchen, and in 15 BBY, he hired two [[Waiter/Legends|waiters]] through the [[Intergalactic Droid Agency]]: the [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and the [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]] [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]].<ref name="The Lost Prince" />

When the [[Droid/Legends|droids]] arrived at the eatery one morning, Sharpelz immediately put them to work.<ref name="Storybook" /> He grew frustrated when the two had trouble remembering orders, repeatedly tripped over each other,<ref name="The Lost Prince" /> and proved to be the worst waiters that the locals had ever seen.<ref name="Tales of the Golden Droid">''[[C-3PO: Tales of the Golden Droid]]''</ref> Late in the [[Standard day/Legends|day]],<ref name="Storybook" /> C-3PO spilled some powder on Sharpelz's face, and the chef angrily sent him to serve Zellock. When the [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord's]] henchman [[Yorpo Mog]] tripped over R2-D2 and landed in Zellock's food, Mog threw the [[R2-series astromech droid/Legends|astromech]] across the café. R2-D2 crashed into both C-3PO and Sharpelz, and the chef responded by immediately firing his new waiters, tossing them out into the street, and telling them never to return.<ref name="The Lost Prince" />

==Personality and traits==
{{Quote|Go and look after Mr. Kleb. He owns a piece of everything in town, including this place. Give him any trouble and I'll melt you down into spittoons!|Doodnik, to C-3PO|<ref name="The Lost Prince" />}}
Doodnik Sharpelz was a gruff and greasy chef with [[Color/Legends|orange]] skin,<ref name="CSWE" /> black [[Eye/Legends|pupils]],<ref name="The Lost Prince" /> and four brawny [[Limb/Legends|arms]].<ref name="CSWE" /> He employed all of his upper limbs while preparing food, during which he was able to perform four different tasks simultaneously.<ref name="The Lost Prince" /> Hardened by fringe life,<ref name="Re-Animated Part 2" /> Sharpelz was intolerant of incompetence in his kitchen and was quick to anger. He threatened to melt C-3PO shortly before furiously firing both the [[3PO-series protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] and his astromech companion. Sharpelz took care to provide good service to Kleb Zellock, who owned a stake in the café, but he did not take care to keep the establishment clean.<ref name="The Lost Prince" />

Sharpelz came to Tyne's Horky full of gastronomic dreams.<ref name="Re-Animated Part 2" /> A skilled bartender, he mixed a photon fizzle that Dexter Jettster believed was unrivaled. Circuit [[Cider/Legends|cider]] was another of his signature drinks. Sharpelz always served giva jumbos in bowls, although Jettster could not figure out why. All in all, Jettster thought his comrade a fine fellow.<ref name="Dining at Dex's" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Because of their obvious similarities, I wanted to imply some kind of connection between Dexter and Doodnik when I was writing this piece. At one point, I think I might have even considered making them brothers, but in the end I decided to leave things more vague.|Gregory Walker, on the development of ''Dining at Dex's''|<ref name="Texas Ranger">{{JCFCite|url=posts/30656900|board=Literature|thread=Hyperspace New Short Fiction: "Dining at Dex's" & Xim Week & new Alex Winger story now online!|user=[[Gregory Walker|NarbFlick]]|date=2009-12-30|time=5:00 AM|archiveurl=https://archive.is/VnbQm}}</ref>}}
The character of Doodnik first appeared in "[[The Lost Prince]]," the fifth episode of the [[Star Wars: Droids: The Adventures of R2-D2 and C-3PO|''Star Wars: Droids'']] animated television series. Written by [[Peter Sauder]] and directed by [[Raymond Jafelice]],<ref name="The Lost Prince" /> the episode first aired on [[October 5]], [[1985]].<ref name="Cel">{{InsiderCite|27|A Star Wars CELibration|A ''Star Wars'' CELibration}}</ref>

[[File:Dextersface.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Dexter Jettster: Not quite Doodnik Sharpelz's brother]]
Author [[Tim Veekhoven]] has surmised that Doodnik and his café influenced the designs of Dexter Jettster and his [[Dex's Diner/Legends|diner]], which were seen in the [[2002]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].<ref name="Boonta to Baobab">{{SW|url=news/from-boonta-to-baobab-droids-and-the-star-wars-prequels|text=From Boonta to Baobab: ''Droids'' and the ''Star Wars'' Prequels|nolive=1}}</ref> The short story "[[Dining at Dex's]]," written by [[Gregory Walker]] and published online through [[StarWars.com]]'s [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] feature in [[2009]], describes Doodnik as an old friend of Jettster. Walker tied the two characters together due to what he believed were obvious similarities between them, and he originally considered making them brothers, thereby establishing Doodnik's species as Besalisk. He ultimately left their relationship vague and did not reveal Doodnik's species,<ref name="Texas Ranger" /> although he did name the character's home planet as the Besalisk homeworld of Ojom.<ref name="Dining at Dex's" /> Despite striking visual differences between Doodnik and the Besalisks, Walker yet believed that Doodnik could plausibly have been a member of that species.<ref name="Texas Ranger" />

Doodnik was finally established as being a member of the Jillsarian species in the [[2013]] article ''[[The Droids Re-Animated]]'', written by [[Abel G. Peña]] and [[Rich Handley]] for the [[StarWars.com]] blog. The article also provided the character with a last name: Sharpelz.<ref name="Re-Animated Part 2" /> Peña and Handley had wanted to make the Jillsarian [[Retroactive continuity|retcon]] for years, but with the release of "Dining at Dex's," Peña was concerned that it would be difficult to disassociate Doodnik from the heavy implication that he was a Besalisk. As the Besalisk connection had not been airtight, however, he ultimately went with what he has described as a "near-flawless" connection and a "perfect" retcon. Peña also praised Walker's work and asserted that he would have made Doodnik a Besalisk if he had not known about Jillsarians.<ref name="Abel speaks">{{JCFCite|url=posts/50854114|board=Literature|thread=What's This? More Droids from Handley and Peña?|user=[[Abel G. Peña|Halagad_Ventor]]|date=2013-07-11|time=5:30 PM|archiveurl=https://archive.is/2jOvt}}</ref>

